OL,3,CHow rare was the Channel Islands
OL,4,C'white Christmas'?
OL,6,FIn 1962 however, 5cm of snow fell in
OL,7,FGuernsey, while there was only a snow
OL,8,Fshower in Jersey, and again nothing
OL,9,Fstuck.
OL,11,FThere is also an unofficial mention of
OL,12,Fsnowfall in Jersey on Christmas Day
OL,13,F1830, before official weather records
OL,14,Fbegan.
OL,16,FA local diary noted 'a very heavy
OL,17,Fsnowfall' on Christmas Day, but the
OL,18,Ftemperature was above 0C and the snow
OL,19,Fdisappeared by 27 December so it was
OL,20,Fshort-lived.
