OL,3,CHow rare was the Channel Islands
OL,4,C'white Christmas'?
OL,6,FScholars believe it is due to a very
OL,7,Fcold decade in the UK in the 1810s,
OL,8,Fwhen prominent author Charles Dickens
OL,9,Fgrew up.
OL,11,FWhen Dickens sat down to write his
OL,12,Fnovels, they were filled with the
OL,13,Ffrosty and snowy memories of what
OL,14,FChristmas looked like back in his
OL,15,Fchildhood.
OL,17,FHow common is snow?
OL,19,FSnow isn't a common feature of our
OL,20,Fweather in the Channel Islands.
