OL,3,CHow rare was the Channel Islands
OL,4,C'white Christmas'?
OL,6,FAs we are surrounded by the sea, which
OL,7,Fhas an insulating effect, our
OL,8,Ftemperatures are milder than those of
OL,9,Flarge bodies of land.
OL,11,FWe are also situated further south
OL,12,Fthan the UK, again making us less
OL,13,Flikely to see those cold temperatures
OL,14,Frequired for snow.
OL,16,FAlthough a 'white Christmas' in the
OL,17,FChannel Islands is rare, a wet one is
OL,18,Fmore common.
